1.	What is PHP?
•	PHP: Hypertext Preprocessor	
•	PHP scripts are executed on the server
•	PHP files can contain text, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and PHP code
•	PHP files have extension ".php
2.	WHAT PHP DO
Generate Dynamic content
Can create, Delete, read, write, open and close
Encrypt data
Collect form data
Send data to cookes
3.	Benfits
•	Php run on platforms Windows, Mos , linux unix 
•	Compatable with almost all servers

SET UP PHP
Install web server
Install PHP
Install Database such as Mysql

LAMP
Linux, Apache, MySQL, PHP	Linux
WAMP
Windows, Apache, MySQL, PHP	Windows
MAMP
Macintosh, Apache, MySQL, PHP	macOS
XAMPP
Cross-Platform, Apache, MariaDB, PHP, Perl	Windows, macOS, and Linux


BASIC PHP SYNTAX
Php script start with <?php end with ?>

Default php file extension is .php
Comments the line(ignore the code)
Single line command //hi I am here
Double line command /* ---this commented line on code ----*/

VARIABLES
•	A variable starts with the $ sign, followed by the name of the variable
•	A variable name must start with a letter or the underscore character
•	A variable name cannot start with a number
•	A variable name can only contain alpha-numeric characters and underscores (A-z, 0-9, and _ )
•	Variable names are case-sensitive ($age and $AGE are two different variables)



OUTPUT VARIABLE
he PHP echo statement is often used to output data to the screen.

